13/07/2010
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Police have arrested one more person in connection with an attack last month on a police station in Bugojno that claimed the life of one police officer, federal police director Zlatko Miletic announced on Monday (July 12th).
Miletic told members of parliament's security committee that this suspect will likely be charged with complicity.
Five other people have been detained in connection with the incident so far.
(BHRT, Radio Free Europe, RTRS - 12/07/10)
